From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Wed, 4 Feb 2026 20:13:10 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: cix: Add msi-parent to PCIe SMMU for MSI-based
 events

The MMU-700 reports IDR0.MSI=1, supporting MSI-based delivery of
event queue, command queue sync, and global error interrupts.
Without msi-parent, the driver falls back to wired IRQs and prints:

  "msi_domain absent - falling back to wired irqs"

Add msi-parent pointing to the PCIe ITS, which is the only ITS on
the SoC. This enables MSI-based interrupt delivery for lower latency
SMMU event and fault reporting.
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1.dtsi | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1.dtsi
index bcffb970f492a..8f4f18d1a185f 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1.dtsi
@@ -667,6 +667,7 @@ smmu_pciehub: iommu@b010000 {
 			<GIC_SPI 76 IRQ_TYPE_EDGE_RISING 0>,
 			<GIC_SPI 80 IRQ_TYPE_EDGE_RISING 0>;
 		interrupt-names = "eventq", "priq", "cmdq-sync", "gerror";
+		msi-parent = <&its_pcie>;
 		dma-coherent;
 		/* Pre-install bypass STEs for PCIe root port and common device SIDs
 		 * to prevent F_TRANSL_FORBIDDEN events during early boot before
